title: Seller Beware
text:
I was excited to order this, but I received the wrong item and requested a refund. The refund was approved but I was required to ship the item back within 7 days (even though it was personalized). I shipped the item back the following day and had to pay quite a bit for return shipping. I requested that the seller refund me for the item and the return shipping since they were the ones who sent the wrong item.
I received my first refund and it only covered the cost of the return shipping and not the item. So I reached out again. Then they sent me a second refund for a random amount that was about half of what I paid for the item. So I reached out again and this time Amazon got involved and guaranteed my full refund as long as I provided the return shipping receipt. I finally got my full refund.
The seller never replied to any of my messages - they just sent random refund installments with zero communication.
I took a risk and repurchased the item and this time it was correct. The white material is THIN and see through but the design is very cute and well done.

Overall I am fairly satisfied with my purchase, but I would say just beware there are some sketchy red flags with the seller and don't expect communication if you need to reach them. Thank goodness for Amazon's refund guarantee!

title: Love the Journal, but the refills...
text:
I was given this journal (I guess you can call it a travelers journal) as a Christmas gift. The smell of the leather is intoxicating and magnificent. Truly, I have been caught sniffing my journal. I have been Bullet Journaling for over two years now, so Im always excited by a new journal, and Ive been hankering for a travelers, so bully for me! If I have some criticizms, it would be this:
1) Closure options. The leather strap looks nice, but functionally is not the best. Ive removed it an am making a bungee style closure for easier access. - Personal preference I guess.
2) No option for a pen loop? Ill look for a travelers accessory to help there.
3) SIZE! So much of the journal market is now A5, or Travelers size. the 5x7 and 6x8 sizes are not really compatible with much.
4) Refills. Ties into the size. I have been scrounging around for a B5 Dot Grid notebook to fill my 5x7 and its Impossible. I don't like lined inserts, so unless I want to make my own, its down to buying the blank ones from Ox&Pine. The paper is OK, but not the best with fountain pens. It would be awesome to buy some Rhodia side stapled notebooks and slide em' on in.

Overall I love the idea, but Ill be reaching out to see if I can reorder in a custom size. The quality is top shelf, the delivery and presentation is impeccable. Just needs to fit my life!

title: Excellent workmanship on a very useful product!
text:
I bought this cover for my Mouse Books, (a subscription-based book club that I supported on Kickstarter.)-- these wonderful little books are a handy pocket size, designed to be read, carried around and shared, but I'm a collector at heart and it bothered me that I was dinging up the corners of my sweet little books.

So I looked for a reasonably priced, no-nonsense, durable cover to keep them safe in my daily travels.
This product fit the bill perfectly!

The leather is just sturdy enough to keep the books safe but supple and very comfortable to handle.
--I can protect both covers of one book by inserting one into each flap and only have the pages exposed.
--I can fit two books if I wish, (but that makes it a little too bulky for my taste.)
--I can insert just one book cover in the back flap and use the other flap for a note card when I want to jot down a bit of inspiration.
--I could not ask for a more perfect fit!

As to the quality of the workmanship and materials ... TOP NOTCH!
The stitching is gorgeous, well matched to the leather and professionally applied.
The leather is full of character and is a tactile pleasure to handle.

Nothing froufrou about this. It's a practical, elegant and well made product. I'm thrilled with it!

text:
We ordered these to make shelves in our kitchen and in the living room. We wanted something a bit nicer than what we found at the hardware store.

They are very strong and sturdy. I'm sure they'll hold my mugs and plants just fine. But the inside corner of many of them were peeling. We found that some of the brackets weren't square, just as others had pointed out. Finally, the screw holes aren't consistent throughout the brackets, so you have to mark where each screw will go for each bracket. This, paired with them not being square, made the install longer than normal. Overall, they look ok once up, but some brackets do look slightly longer than others. I get that these are handmade, but I guess I expected a bit better craftsmanship.

title: Finally, a book printed on gorgeous paper!
text:
I received both of Molly's newest books yesterday. They are absolutely gorgeous!!! I wish I could thank Molly personally. Since I can't, this will have to do.

The books take a little bit longer to come, I presume because Molly has become the manufacturer. The wait is definitely worth it. The books are now spiral bound at the top of the page. Fantastic for those of us who are lefties!!! Wahoo!!! Thank you Molly!

Now here's the very best part, aside from Molly's gorgeous artwork, the paper. I have said for some time now, along with many other Colorists, that I would pay more for a book with better paper. Well here's your opportunity! Molly is printing her books now, on what I believe is a beautiful multi-purpose paper. I rarely use markers, but I think it will take them beautifully. The tooth of the paper is heavenly. Pencils scream for joy (LOL) when used on this paper. If you wanted to color a masterpiece, here is your opportunity. If you enjoy pencils, you are very going to love Molly's two new books.

The books are different from each other. This one is comprised of her favorite grayscale pictures, and the other her favorite line art pictures. So the art in these books has been pretty printed in her previous books.

If you have never bought any of Molly's books before, I suggest that you start with either this one, or the other other one; which is compromised of her favorite line art.

Yes, these books are a little bit more expensive, but they are what most of us have been asking for, for several years. I can hardly wait to put pencil to paper, but I have another WIP to finish first.

If you are one of many who have been asking the artists to print their books on something other than Create Space paper, today is the day! Have a blessed day and color on!

title: Despite the price, this book is a paperback and the pages are NOT perforated.
text:
Im sorry that I can't agree with the other Colorists about rating this book. I must say first, before I explain why I gave this book only 3 stars, what I really like about this it.
1. The art in this coloring book is probably some of the very best you can find anywhere. If you love coloring people / portraits; then you will fall head over heels in love with this book.
2. The paper is a bright white with an awesome tooth for colored pencils.
3. The pictures are all printed single sided.

Now, here is why I could only give this book 3 stars. Undoubtedly, if you have been thinking about purchasing this book, the price has probably held you back. It took me a little while, before I could save the money for this book. At this price, I expected only the best. Any other books that I have purchased in this price range, have a few things in common that this book lacks. First of all, I expect the book to either be spiral or hard bound. This book is bound like all the other budget friendly books. It is sewn like many other paperback coloring books. That being said, it is a paperback. Next, at this price I definitely expect the pages to be perforated. Books that cost significantly less (around the five dollar mark, for example, Creative Haven coloring books) have perforated pages.

Because the art is this book is so magnificent, I wish that I could rate this book with five stars.

Just because book has such wonderful artwork, doesn't mean that the artist can take advantage of us in pricing it. All in all, if you love coloring portraits of people who are infants to senior citizens, then you should consider be this book. I truly believe that the art in this book is some of the very best that you can find. However, due to the pricing of it, you should carefully consider that it is a paperback like most bargain priced books; and that the pages are not perforated. Because the art is so magnificent, you will probably want to frame several of these pictures, but you will need to cut the pages out, because they are not perforated.

I intend to spend a great deal of time Coloring these pictures - there is not a single "bad" page in the book. I won't post any pictures because several other reviewers already have.

As always, have a blessed day and color on!!!
